calais jungle refugees get a grip france they are visitors they have no rights or in a position to demand europe needs to get a grip
I see a lot of people in Calais who have been living there for years, waiting for a chance to start a new life. They are human beings, deserving of dignity and respect, regardless of their immigration status. Let's focus on finding solutions that prioritize their safety and well-being, rather than demonizing them as "visitors" with no rights.
